{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"moistful-pleased-phoebe","description":"## Why\n\n`compact.emit_legacy_signature_mirror` (default False) is the CONTRACT-phase rollback\nlever of the additive-attestations rollout (epic dark-acme-lumen). Its default already\nmeans \"never emit the legacy `state['signature']` mirror into new snapshots\" â€” so\nremoving it does NOT change runtime behavior. What removal deletes is the documented\none-line ROLLBACK (`= true` + recompact) that re-emits the mirror for a still-live\npre-attestations reader. Approved for removal; this story does it responsibly.\n\n## What\n\n- Remove the field + validator from `CompactConfig` (`_config_schema.py:367` and the\n  parser entry in the `compact` section, `~:515`).\n- Hardcode never-emit in `_snapshot_strip_keys` (`_commands/compact.py:127-136`):\n  always add `\"signature\"` to the dropped-keys set; delete the `emit_legacy_mirror`\n  branch.\n- PRESERVE the in-memory mirror path: `process_signature` re-deriving `state[\"signature\"]`\n  during replay (`reducer/_processors.py:562-604`) and the `most_recent_attestation`\n  fallback (`signing.py:563-568`) stay â€” this story only stops PERSISTING the mirror\n  into new snapshots; it does not touch the in-memory back-compat projection.\n- Doc-sweep coordination: the doc-sweep story removes references; this story updates\n  `docs/migrations.md` \"Legacy signature-mirror retirement\" to record the retirement\n  and that the rollback lever is gone.\n\n## Scope â€” the one-way door (handle, don't skip)\n\nBackward-compat verdict (from assessment): CONDITIONAL. Removal is a ONE-WAY DOOR. It is\nsafe for THIS fleet (hourly auto-update to origin/main â‡’ no pre-attestations binary is\nlive). It WOULD break an external project on older rebar that reads a mirror-less\nsnapshot whose latest signature was compacted below the horizon (the reader sees no\n`signature`, cannot read `attestations`, and the SIGNATURE event is gone) â€” after\nremoval the only recovery is a code downgrade, not a config flip.\n\nTherefore, before landing: assert the readiness gate (`docs/migrations.md:149-156`)\nholds â€” no pre-attestations clone/reconcile-host shares this store â€” and record the\none-way-door retirement in the release notes so any downstream consumer is warned.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `emit_legacy_signature_mirror` removed from schema, parser, and `rebar.toml` (if present); new snapshots never persist the `signature` mirror.\n- [ ] `process_signature` in-memory mirror + `most_recent_attestation` fallback are UNCHANGED (prove with existing signing/replay tests green).\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Readiness gate asserted: no pre-attestations rebar binary reads this store (state the basis â€” e.g. fleet auto-update policy).\n- [ ] `docs/migrations.md` \"Legacy signature-mirror retirement\" updated to record the retirement and removal of the rollback lever; release notes warn downstream consumers of the one-way door.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"7ed9-ae31-a01e-44a9","parent_id":"8d27-7ee1-f137-4b88","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Retire compact.emit_legacy_signature_mirror (hardcode never-emit) after readiness-gate check"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783968651350909001,"uuid":"3039303a-7dc4-4704-97cc-44b846b923f5"}